entity-family-nongraphical-objects — the OBJECTS-section object families
========================================================================

Status: DEFERRED (schms-parity 1.6.6). Parent: entity-mutation-parity.

ENTMAKEX (and dictadd) can create non-graphical OBJECTS-section objects.
Only XRECORD is in the entity-family registry so far. The rest are
accepted permissively (no validation / subclass stamping):

  - DICTIONARY / DICTIONARYVAR / DICTIONARYWDFLT (the tree itself is
    modelled in drawing/source/model.lisp, but ENTMAKEX-creating one
    with proper AcDbDictionary markers + 280/281 flags is not).
  - GROUP (+ the ACAD_GROUP dictionary), LAYER_FILTER / LAYER_INDEX,
    SPATIAL_FILTER / SPATIAL_INDEX, SORTENTSTABLE, IDBUFFER.
  - LAYOUT (+ PLOTSETTINGS), the ACAD_LAYOUT dictionary.
  - MATERIAL, VISUALSTYLE, MLEADERSTYLE, MLINESTYLE, TABLESTYLE,
    SCALE / ACAD_SCALELIST, FIELD / FIELDLIST, RASTERVARIABLES,
    WIPEOUTVARIABLES, ACDBDICTIONARYWDFLT, ACAD_PROXY_OBJECT,
    DATATABLE, GEODATA, SUNSTUDY, ACDBNAVISWORKSMODELDEF.

Do
--

Register descriptors with the correct AcDbObject/AcDb<Type> subclass
markers and required codes, ensure ownership (330) and the reactor
(102 {ACAD_REACTORS} / 102 {ACAD_XDICTIONARY}) groups round-trip, add
tests. These are model-only (no rendering, no persistence-format work
beyond what drawing/source/dxf.lisp already round-trips).

Reference: AutoCAD DXF reference, OBJECTS section.
